.TH PRINTF 1 "25/11/2024" "version 1.0" "user commands"
.SH NAME
printf \- format and print data
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.B \fBprintf\fR FORMAT [ARGUMENT]...
.PP
.B \fBprintf\fR OPTION
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
The \fBprintf\fR command is used to format and display text and numbers with precise formatting control, similar to the printf function in the C language.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B %c: prints a single character
.TP
.B %s: prints a string of characters
.TP
.B %d: prints a decimal number
.TP
.B %i: prints an integer in base 10
.TP
.B %%: prints a percent sign

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.B for the %c
.nf
.B printf("Caractère : %c\n", 'A');
.fi
.PP
.B for the %s
.nf
.B printf("Chaîne : %s\n", "Bonjour");
.fi
.PP
.B for the %d
.nf
.B printf("Nombre décimal : %d\n", 42);
.fi
.PP
.B for the %i
.nf
.B printf("Entier : %i\n", 123);
.fi
.PP
.B for the %%
.nf
.B printf("Pourcentage : %%\n");
.fi
.SH AUTHOR
 Written by Yassine BOUYANIF, Luca Mansi
